summarize stats output (compute quantiles)

Source: R/tidyMS_stats.R
summarize_stats_quantiles.Rd

summarize stats output (compute quantiles)

summarize_stats_quantiles(
  stats_res,
  config,
  stats = c("sd", "CV"),
  probs = c(0.1, 0.25, 0.5, 0.75, 0.9)
)

Arguments

stats_res

result of running `summarize_stats`
config

AnalysisConfiguration
stats

summarize either sd or CV
probs

for which quantiles 10, 20 etc.

See also

Other stats: INTERNAL_FUNCTIONS_BY_FAMILY, compute_pooled(), lfq_power_t_test_proteins(), lfq_power_t_test_quantiles_V2(), lfq_power_t_test_quantiles(), plot_stat_density_median(), plot_stat_density(), plot_stat_violin_median(), plot_stat_violin(), plot_stdv_vs_mean(), poolvar(), summarize_stats_all(), summarize_stats()

#> Column added : nr_peptide_Id_IN_protein_Id
config <- bb1$config$clone( deep = TRUE)
data <- bb1$data
stats_res <- summarize_stats(data, config)
#> completing cases
